question: Wedding dress shopping!
answer:
OOh dress shopping!!!

_____________________

For the dress shopping you got yourself a little entourage to help you pick a dress. You weren’t really sure what dress you wanted. So you could really use your mother, sister, best friend, Anne and Gemma’s help.

You all arrived at this little bridal boutique just outside the city of London. One of your co-workers had recommended this shop since she found her dress there too.

You entered and immediately you were in awe with all the beautiful dresses that were displayed in the shop.

You immediately went your seperate way to a dress that catches your eyes. It was this very simple yet elegant dress with lace around the shoulders.

‘Hello everybody, can I help with anything?’ You heard a woman’s voice say and you turned around. ‘Yes, I am looking for a wedding dress.’ You said. ‘Anything in particular that you are looking for?’ The woman whose name was apparently Wendy asked.

‘Well, I really love this dress.’ You say and point at the dress that you were just standing by.

‘It’s really pretty YN.’ Anne says.

‘It is, well if you like that one I think I have two other dresses that you may like.’ Wendy says. ‘Would you like to try them on?’ She asked and you nodded. ‘Well, let me get them for you. Your entourage can sit down there.’ Wendy said and pointed at a place in the shop where there were couches.

‘And you can follow me to the dressing room.’ Wendy pointed at you and you followed her to the back of the store. Before you turned the corner you waved at your entourage and your sister, best friend and Gemma gave you a thumbs up.

‘So, YN I got you the dress you saw in the store, then I have this dress with a longer sleeve and a belt in the center and then finally this more off-white dress with no lace but the same style as the first one.’ ‘Should we start with the one you picked out?’ Wendy asked and you nodded. You tried on the dress and you fell tears in your eyes. The dress was really beautiful and the style was really flattering for your figure.

‘Ready to show the rest?’ Wendy asked with a small smile on her face. ‘Yes.’ you said and rubbed your eyes to get rid of the glossiness.

When you walked out everybody smiled. ‘You look beautiful YN.’ Your mom said and you smiled at her. ‘I really love the dress!’ Gemma said. ‘Oh god I am crying!’ Your best friend said and you could feel the tears in your eyes again.

‘Well it seems like you all love the dress a lot. There are tissues at the side table over there.’ Wendy said with a little laugh. ‘I don’t know what is happening to me, I keep crying in this dress.’ You said while drying your tears, this comment made everybody laugh.

‘That is a good sign darling.’ Anne said.

‘Would you like to try on the other two dresses I picked?’ Wendy asked and you nodded, but you knew they weren’t going to top this dress. And apparently you weren’t the only one who thought the first one was the best. The other dresses were also very beautiful but your dress had something that you just couldn’t describe.

‘Well, if only all my customers were as easy as you YN.’ Wendy said when you were all standing at her desk. ‘I didn’t think I would find the dress so fast. Normally it takes me longer to find clothes.’ You said and your sister laughed at that and added ‘Yes, that’s true.’

‘So, your dress will be ready next month and then you can come back to do  a final fitting.’ Wendy said and you all thanked her.

You walked out the store with the biggest smile on your face because you just bought yourself the most amazing wedding dress.

blog.title: I'm Gin.
blog.description: •●○☆ Quasi-Astrologer • Nature Lover • Harry Styles Enthusiast ☆○●•

summary: How does Harry having his moon in the 12th house affect him?
question: How does Harry having his moon in the 12th house affect him?
answer:
It means he’s sensitive, he’s moody, he’s gentle and kind, he’s a secret do-gooder, he has secret affairs he’ll never tell people about. Secrets, especially of the emotional variety, are sort of his thing, in general. 

The thing about the 12th house is the planet that resides in it is sort of going at it all from the blind spot of the chart native. The planet still functions, but the chart native can’t SEE the functions of the planet. Often times, neither can anyone else. The chart native can only see the results of the planet, again, because it’s in his blind spot. He may not fully understand why he behaves the way he does when it comes to his emotions. Chances are, he knows he’s the way he is, but he’s just at a loss as to why. 

Harry’s moon is well aspected by his mars, sun and Venus. This means his actions, his ego, and his loves are all touched by his secret emotions. Harry will always be private. He’ll always physically do things we will never hear about, unless he wants us to hear about them. He can be egotistical, but if he doesn’t want people to see his ego, they won’t. Harry will have many loves that we never know the names of, unless he wants us to. In the moment, when these things are happening, he almost always prefers to keep them secret. I think people with this placement do this because of the fact that they themselves don’t know exactly how to emotionally maneuver the situation in real time, and so what they do is allow the situation to happen and unfold as it happens, and then they have to go off in some way on their own and process the emotions that came from the situation. These people normally learn to play it very safe, especially as they get older. 

When they’re younger, they’ll probably be slightly rash, not stopping to think about how their actions might affect others.

The things about someone with a placement like this, especially in a sign like Libra, is that they need things to be just and fair. It would probably make them sick to know that they did anything to another human being that was unfair, so they would go out of their way to make it right. Harry’s kindness is NOT an act. He really has a very gentle soul. When he tears up randomly on stage or when he gets to sing with his idol or when he hears something that he knows isn’t true and it hurts him, those are real tears. Now, Harry is smart, and cunning, and he knows how to play a crowd and manipulate to his advantage, but those spontaneous unrehearsed moments where he wells up out of nowhere and you hear the emotion thicken his voice, that’s all real. 

He’s probably had to work really hard at accepting the fact that just is.. emotional. He’s also probably worked pretty hard to structure his life in a way that emotional situations don’t happen everytime he turns around. 

People with 12th house placements need a lot of time to themselves to recoup. While he has the energy to handle the concerts and tours, I’d imagine behind closed doors, especially later in the tour, he really suffers. It will all start to get to him after awhile, even though he literally loves it like nothing else. 

Harry’s probably a lot more charitable than any of us could ever imagine. He probably sees the injustices of the world and wonders why the hell he was the one to make it, and what can he do to make someone else’s life easier? If he was chosen for whatever reason, to be in this position, he’s going to stop at nothing to make the world a better place. It’s the least he can do, in his mind.

I have my moon in the 6th house in Aries (in his and my chart, we have the same rising within a degree in Libra), and if I was around him, I’d probably body check people on a regular basis in an attempt to protect him, which he’d hate because he’d feel it wasn’t fair to them. I don’t think many people will ever know quite how gentle Harry really is, deep down, but with this placement, and with it well aspected, he’d have to be.

He’s probably had to work really hard at accepting the fact that just is.. emotional. He’s also probably worked pretty hard to structure his life in a way that emotional situations don’t happen everytime he turns around. 

People with 12th house placements need a lot of time to themselves to recoup. While he has the energy to handle the concerts and tours, I’d imagine behind closed doors, especially later in the tour, he really suffers. It will all start to get to him after awhile, even though he literally loves it like nothing else. 

Harry’s probably a lot more charitable than any of us could ever imagine. He probably sees the injustices of the world and wonders why the hell he was the one to make it, and what can he do to make someone else’s life easier? If he was chosen for whatever reason, to be in this position, he’s going to stop at nothing to make the world a better place. It’s the least he can do, in his mind.

I have my moon in the 6th house in Aries (in his and my chart, we have the same rising within a degree in Libra), and if I was around him, I’d probably body check people on a regular basis in an attempt to protect him, which he’d hate because he’d feel it wasn’t fair to them. I don’t think many people will ever know quite how gentle Harry really is, deep down, but with this placement, and with it well aspected, he’d have to be.

It means he’s sensitive, he’s moody, he’s gentle and kind, he’s a secret do-gooder, he has secret affairs he’ll never tell people about. Secrets, especially of the emotional variety, are sort of his thing, in general. 

The thing about the 12th house is the planet that resides in it is sort of going at it all from the blind spot of the chart native. The planet still functions, but the chart native can’t SEE the functions of the planet. Often times, neither can anyone else. The chart native can only see the results of the planet, again, because it’s in his blind spot. He may not fully understand why he behaves the way he does when it comes to his emotions. Chances are, he knows he’s the way he is, but he’s just at a loss as to why. 

Harry’s moon is well aspected by his mars, sun and Venus. This means his actions, his ego, and his loves are all touched by his secret emotions. Harry will always be private. He’ll always physically do things we will never hear about, unless he wants us to hear about them. He can be egotistical, but if he doesn’t want people to see his ego, they won’t. Harry will have many loves that we never know the names of, unless he wants us to. In the moment, when these things are happening, he almost always prefers to keep them secret. I think people with this placement do this because of the fact that they themselves don’t know exactly how to emotionally maneuver the situation in real time, and so what they do is allow the situation to happen and unfold as it happens, and then they have to go off in some way on their own and process the emotions that came from the situation. These people normally learn to play it very safe, especially as they get older. 

When they’re younger, they’ll probably be slightly rash, not stopping to think about how their actions might affect others.

The things about someone with a placement like this, especially in a sign like Libra, is that they need things to be just and fair.
